	('a14c55ac-bfdc-4c40-8882-7dc586aeeb93', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', '46870047', 'Sales Scripts for Stores.docx', 'docx', 'Welcome

Greet every guest within 20 seconds of entering the store at either entrance.

“Hey, how are you today?”  Respond with a helpful/inspiring question. For instance, “Are you shopping for an event in particular?” or “We have some great pieces that would look great on you, would it be alright for me to pull a few down and set up a dressing room for you?”

Free People Area

”Did you know that we’re a Free People Shop-in-Shop?”

If customer says no:  “Well a Free People Shop-in-Shop means that we carry such a large selection of Free People items that we are considered our own Free People store.  We sell not only clothing, but shoes and intimates as well.  However, we are locally owned and operated store not associated with Urban Outfitters stores.”

If customer says yes:  “Well great!  That means you know we carry a large selection of Free People items including shoes and intimates.  If you have trouble finding anything, just let me know.”

Be sure sales rep suggests a best-seller, new arrival, or a personal favorite from the FP area.

Shoes

“Have you ever shopped our shoes before?”

If customer says no:  “Well just so you know, all our shoes are on the floor and open stock meaning you are welcome to browse for your own sizes near the style you like, but I’m here to assist you if needed.  Also, our shoe wall hides all the extra sizes, so be sure to pull on the book to find your size.”  Demonstrate how to open the cabinet.

If customer says yes:  “Fantastic.  That means you know all our sizes on the floor and to pull on the book to find the size you need on the shoe wall. (Demonstrate)  If you need help finding your size or have any questions, be sure to let me know.”

Be sure to suggest a best-seller, new arrival, or a personal favorite from shoes.

Near Candles

“Do you know about Aspen Bay candles?”

If customer says no:  “Aspen Baby candles are actually made in Starkville.  It’s a soy-based candle that smells fantastic and burn forever.  The large candles will burn for over 80 hours!”

If customer says yes:  “Have you ever purchased one?” 

Yes: “Well great!  Then you know how awesome they are.  Libby’s favorite scent is Sueded Tobacco so we try to always burn one at the register.  What’s your favorite scent?”

No:  “Well be sure to check out our selection.   Libby’s favorite scent is Sueded Tobacco so we burn one at the register a lot.  It smells up the entire store!! My favorite scent is _______ and that’s what I use at home.  Which scent do you like most?”

Jacob Davis Jeans Area

“Have you heard of Jacob Davis jeans before?”

If customer says no:  “Just so you know, Jacob Davis jeans are manufactured in the same place as Level 99 jeans, so you get the same quality jean without the same price tag.  They’re super soft, pretty stretchy, and most styles come in a 31” inseam.  Would you like to try a pair on?”

If customer says yes: “Great!  Then you know they’re manufactured by Level 99 so you get the same quality jean without the price of Level 99.  Which style is your favorite?  (wait on customer to respond)  We try to always keep styles and sizes fully stocked.  Would you like to try a pair on?”

Be sure to suggest a best-seller, new arrival, or a personal favorite from Jacob Davis jeans.

Near Jewelry Area

“Did you know that we carry a large selection of handmade jewelry?”

If customer says no:  “Oh, well let me tell you about a few of our handmade lines.  (Start by taking customer towards jewelry cases)  All of our items in the cases are handmade goods.  Prices of pieces in the case range from about $32-50.  

Nakamol is line out of Chicago that is most known by our customers for their wrap bracelets.  However, they make necklaces and earrings too.  They use real leather and semi-precious stones and beading for all of their goods.  

Flea Market Girl jewelry pieces combine raw minerals, semi precious stones, bronze, leather, and brass metal. The style of this combination creates an array of looks for the line, from edgy to dainty, which is expected to make the quintessential “flea market girl” feel confident in her own style.  

(Lead customer away from cases towards Lo Lady)  Lo Lady necklaces are made by a local Jackson artist in Fondren.  Lauren tries to create vintage-inspired pieces that are upcycled and made from 80-100 year old artwork pieces.  

But not everything we carry is handmade.  We have a wide variety of brands and styles throughout this section here.  Necklaces are all in this area and earrings and bangles are located on the table right there. (Hand suggest to appropriate areas)  This piece right here is one  ______ (of my favorites, of our best sellers, or is absolute must-have.”

If customer says yes:  “Great!  Then you know we stock a large selection of Nakamol, Flea Market Girl, and Lo Lady handmade goods, plus a wide variety of other jewelry lines.  This piece right here is one ______ (of my favorites, of our best sellers, or is absolute must-have.”

Clearance/Sale Room

“Do you know about our sale?”

If customer says no:  “Ok, well let me tell you about our sale going on today.  All items in this area are  _____ (whatever the sale may be).  The sale area is divided up with our $10-20 rack here, and then all tops are here and bottoms are here.  We try to keep everything sized within in each section, but if you can’t find the size you’re looking for, just let me know and I’ll see what I can find for you.”  (Sales rep needs to be in the sale room with customer explaining the layout and sale)

If customer says yes:  “Ok, great! Then you know that _______ (this is the sale going on).  Also, just in case you don’t know, the sale area is divided up with our $10-20 rack here, and then all tops are here and bottoms are here.  We try to keep everything sized within in each section, but if you can’t find the size you’re looking for, just let me know and I’ll see what I can find for you.”  (Sales rep needs to be in the sale room with customer explaining the layout and sale)

Dresses Area

“Are you looking for a dress for a specific occasion?” 

If customer says no:  “Well just so you know, all of our dresses are located within this section here, except for our Free People dresses which are located in our Free People section at the front.  If you can’t find your size, just let me know.  I can always check our mannequins and inventory at our Starkville location to see if we have the size you need.”

If customer says yes:  “Oh great! Well what occasion are you shopping for?  I might be able to make some suggestions.”  (Let customer explain)  “Is there a particular style or color you’re looking for?” (Let customer explain and then make recommendations based on occasion/styles the customer described.)

    MinkPink/Some Days Lovin Area

“Are you familiar with the brands MinkPink and Some Days Lovin?”

If customer says no:  “MinkPink is actually an Australian based brand, and we’re one of the only retailers for it in the Jackson area.  MinkPink is super quirky, fashion-forward, and base their clothing for the season around different themes.  This season’s theme is a _____ (90’s rock, Japanese, etc. whatever theme may be)-inspired collection.  And, Some Days Lovin is actually a sister brand to MinkPink.   Some Days Lovin is for your girly-girl that loves travel and talks to strangers.   Both brands are super eclectic and a perfect fit for our stores.  This is one of our _____ (new arrivals, best sellers, personal favorites) and it looks great styled with this….”

If customer says yes:  “Great, then I know you recognize their super quirky, fashion forward pieces.  This is one of our _____ (new arrivals, best sellers, personal favorites) and it looks great styled with this….”

Swim Area

“Have you had a chance to try on any of our swimwear yet?”

If customer says no:  “Well just so you know you can mix and match any style and sizes.  Also, all of our brands run a little on the small size, so don’t hesitate to try a size up.  Plus, mostly all the Maaji brand styles are reversible, so you can actually have 2 different looks with one suit.  Let’s take a look and pull some styles you like to try on.”

If customer says yes:  “Great! Then you know you can mix and match, plus it all runs a little small. And don’t forget, that most of the Maaji ones are reversible.  Do you see any styles you’d like to try on?”

Dressing Room Area

Once your customer is ready to try on:

“Do you follow us on Instagram or Facebook?”

If customer says no:  “Oh, well you should look us up! You can actually shop straight from our Instagram/Facebook  pages by signing up for social shopping .  It’s super easy!  In fact, you sign up for social shopping by filling out this form here (direct to form in DR on clipboard), and when you’re checking out, we’ll put your credit card on file.  Don’t worry, it’s only attached to your name in our computer system, so you’ll be the only one that can authorize charges, and if you sign up today, you get 10% off one item at the register when you’re checking out!”

If customer says yes:  “Well do you know about social shopping?”

If customer says no:  “Well social shopping means you can shop straight from our Instagram/Facebook  pages.  It’s super easy!  In fact, you sign up for social shopping by filling out this form here (direct to form in DR on clipboard), and when you’re checking out, we’ll put your credit card on file.  Don’t worry, it’s only attached to your name in our computer system, so you’ll be the only one that can authorize charges, and if you sign up today, you get 10% off one item at the register!”

If customer says yes:  “Well then, you should sign up for social shopping today by filling out this form here (direct to form in DR on clipboard) and when you’re checking out, we’ll put your credit card on file.  Don’t worry, it’s only attached to your name in our computer system, so you’ll be the only one that can authorize charges, and if you sign up today, you get 10% off one item at the register!”

If customer says they’re already signed up for social shopping:  “Great!  Then you’re already all set up to shop straight from Instagram/Facebook.  We post all of our new arrivals there first, so you’ve got first dibs on all our best items!”

Once your customer is in the DR and trying-on:

“Be sure to let me know if you need a basic piece like a lace bra, bandeau, cami or slip.  We have a great selection out here, and I’ve already put a few in your room to try on with pieces you chose.  If I didn’t get the right size or style you needed, please don’t hesitate to ask for a different one.”

At Checkout

First - “Hi! Did you find everything you needed today?”  (Wait on customer response and respond accordingly)  

Second - “Have you ever shopped with us before?”  

If customer says yes:  “Great, what name are you under in our system?”

Always verify the city/phone number of the person in system.  Update address info if needed.  

NEVER search by customer number unless a last resource.  Most of the time, customers do not remember what phone number it’s under in the system and it’s a waste of time to try to search that way, plus it’s VERY IMPERSONAL.

If the customer has two different customer accounts (either mom/daughter, sisters, or a duplicate), always recommend to use just one account due to loyalty point accumulation.  Let Rachel know the name and number (write it down) associated with a duplicate account so we can delete the one that is not being used.  

If customer says yes, but they are not in our system:  “Well just so you know, you’re missing out on a lot of perks of our Customer Loyalty Program.  It’s just a free rewards and program.  Are you sure you don’t want to join today so you can receive loyalty points for your purchase today?”

If customer says no – just keep checking out.

If customer says yes  – add to system.

If customer says no:  “Would you like to join our Customer Loyalty Program?  It’s not like a credit card.  It’s just a FREE rewards and perks program! You earn money back on your purchases, you’re the first to know about new arrivals, sales, and promotions, and you get a birthday discount during your birthday month!  It only takes about 2 minutes to get signed up.  Are you interested in joining today?”

If customer says no – just keep checking out.

If customer says yes  – add to system.

Put customer in system underneath their phone number.

Always enter a first and last name.

Always enter a current, physical mailing address.  

Try to get an email address.  

If the customer does not want to give you an email address, inform them that they will miss out on discounts, including their birthday discount.

Get their birthday month too (but is not necessary if they won’t give their email address).

If a customer says yes (but we are super busy and there is a line at the register) – add to system.

Only enter customer phone number and name.  

Give them a customer info card to fill out while you finish checking them out with all other information, so we can enter it at a later time.

Third – Inform customer of any kind of promo we have going on at that time and attach flyer to receipt/or put in bag with receipt.  

