	('fc2dea57-3a58-40f7-9296-872bcc53608d', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', 'dff436db-cd86-41d2-90e2-77d04a660e8b', 'Complaint Resolution and Recovery Statistics | Critical data on how effective complaint resolution can recover customer relationships and the consequences of poor service recovery. | The Power of Quick Resolution | 95% of complaining customers will return if you resolve their complaint instantly. If resolved favorably but not immediately, 70% will still return. However, it takes 12 positive service incidents to make up for one negative experience. | Communication as Root Cause | 80% of complaints stem from poor communication, either with customers or within the organization. In 73% of cases where customers left, no attempt was made to retain them, even though 35% said a simple apology would have prevented their departure. | Word-of-Mouth Impact | Dissatisfied customers tell 9-16 people about their negative experience, with 13-20% telling more than 20 people. In contrast, customers with resolved problems tell 4-6 people about their positive experience. This highlights the disproportionate impact of negative versus positive word-of-mouth.', '948331d9eceb3166', '[-0.015874881,0.03494817,0.06430147,0.038861733,-0.030814918,-0.010737394,0.051732242,0.06538376,0.025815878,-0.06674688,0.056593787,0.03098098,0.06969606,0.0077358307,0.05209212,-0.050398063,0.079135306,-0.010509133,-0.13398667,0.0061168824,-0.029438183,0.0024282187,-0.03579296,0.044522393,-0.05074542,-0.050395202,-0.06418279,0.0094501665,-0.006658061,-0.03843553,-0.049551778,0.1280891,0.057898466,0.001938853,-0.024681628,0.07851823,-0.031372853,-0.030714894,-0.020392898,-0.055616636,-0.0005127609,-0.005438004,-0.01908383,-0.023322498,0.04630338,-0.040168133,0.03990258,0.11989634,-0.036447264,0.0004705278,-0.020584542,0.016742691,-0.009878491,0.023023877,0.00038065863,0.0071973745,-0.037515014,0.025991421,-0.07498294,0.06987739,0.004721791,-0.096398786,-0.014838279,-0.0160052,0.