	('1de4e395-b0d1-46dc-ad6e-a9078d336fb6', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', '3bea755f-2169-4648-b494-46ac78c91fcc', 'Dressing Room Service and Social Media Engagement | Role: Manager | Comprehensive process for providing exceptional dressing room service while promoting social shopping enrollment to increase digital engagement and sales. | Social Media Assessment | When customer is ready to try on items, ask ''Do you follow us on Instagram or Facebook?'' to gauge their current social media engagement with the store. | Decision: Social Media Following Status | Tailor approach based on customer''s social media engagement level | Social Shopping Enrollment Process | Direct customer to form in dressing room on clipboard. Explain: ''You sign up for social shopping by filling out this form here, and when you''re checking out, we''ll put your credit card on file. Don''t worry, it''s only attached to your name in our computer system, so you''ll be the only one that can authorize charges, and if you sign up today, you get 10% off one item at the register!'' | Provide Dressing Room Support | Once customer is in dressing room, offer: ''Be sure to let me know if you need a basic piece like a lace bra, bandeau, cami or slip. We have a great selection out here, and I''ve already put a few in your room to try on with pieces you chose. If I didn''t get the right size or style you needed, please don''t hesitate to ask for a different one.'' | Monitor and Assist | Regularly check on customer''s fitting progress, offer styling advice, suggest additional pieces, and ensure they have everything needed for a complete outfit.', 'dab455d1460d8967', '[-0.07157328,-0.048176333,0.020259306,0.019790709,0.06658528,0.01781013,0.038724113,0.00044671362,0.005328507,-0.053050485,0.08657599,0.039680824,0.021338262,0.000980194,0.13726196,-0.07057469,0.033136804,-0.044997726,-0.040975507,0.0056208544,-0.090485446,-0.05902672,-0.028489836,0.05445948,-0.032650508,-0.07718597,-0.03674946