	('09e7da25-a6df-4ada-b4fe-a7baf9380fe7', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', '77031929-687f-4602-9deb-11ea3cfa7f83', 'Sales Process and Objection Handling Protocol | Role: Lead | Structured approach to managing the sales process from product presentation through closing, including proper objection handling and pacing. | Product Knowledge Verification | Before engaging with customers, verify you know current promotions, pricing for regular inventory items, and key product features. Update yourself on any new arrivals or special offers at the start of each shift. | Paced Product Presentation | Present items at the customer''s pace, avoiding rushing them to purchase. Allow time for browsing, trying on items, and consideration. Focus on showing rather than telling by demonstrating product benefits. | Decision: Handle Customer Objections | Address customer concerns appropriately based on the type of objection raised | Natural Closing Process | Wait for customer buying signals before suggesting purchase. Look for cues like asking about return policies, checking themselves in the mirror repeatedly, or asking about availability in other sizes.', 'e4d37c5de2ca76b5', '[-0.025713414,0.044458926,0.022182275,-0.037740726,0.019463409,0.024344591,0.06397029,0.0693718,0.011058951,-0.01432747,0.02393192,0.05273737,-0.039287753,-0.021357842,0.04335231,0.0068219556,0.062834546,-0.03498099,-0.012375992,0.028145406,0.017532935,0.008976443,-0.0075343605,0.029477172,-0.1566325,-0.008662151,0.017645134,-0.03719362,0.06471827,-0.05467185,-0.014906203,0.030126903,0.045063123,-0.015511662,0.0031713604,0.010767434,0.008348297,-0.031424705,0.006120226,-0.04588747,0.008732119,-0.06551698,-0.14418285,0.018655939,0.06714364,-0.03501515,0.03486132,0.045667082,-0.003419854,0.017720688,-0.09275799,-0.047043897,-0.04281152,-0.006823022,-0.006284774,0.0005018071,0.07356167,-0.057215326,0.0018239191,0.028128441,-0.005925247,-0.08004571,-0.103865705,0.027247034,-0.03388595,0.0952628,-0.03