	('af933461-3b78-4b96-9003-55d984e575d9', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', 'cd2d8373-0d2c-4950-906e-a232d90bb60e', 'Using Power Words in Customer Interactions | Role: New Associate | A step-by-step guide for incorporating the 10 most powerful sales words into customer conversations to increase engagement and sales effectiveness. | Open with ''You'' to personalize the conversation | Begin customer interactions by using ''You'' early in your greeting or presentation. Example: ''You''re going to love our new collection'' or ''This style would look amazing on you.'' This makes the conversation feel more personal and engaging. | Identify customer needs and motivations | Listen to what the customer is looking for and observe their behavior to determine which power words will resonate most. Pay attention to whether they mention comfort, style, occasions, or budget concerns. | Decision: Select appropriate power words based on customer needs | Choose power words that align with customer motivations | Incorporate multiple power words naturally | Weave 2-3 power words into your product presentation. Example: ''You''re going to love how this proven style gives you results that save you time getting ready each morning.'' Ensure the language flows naturally and doesn''t sound forced. | Close with emotional connection | End your presentation using ''Love'' to create emotional attachment. Example: ''Your friends are going to love this look on you'' or ''You''ll love how confident this makes you feel.''', '1a53733ed7ec4cdb', '[-0.06424308,0.04063069,0.02077249,0.039515223,-0.034652475,-0.028674224,0.10916732,0.03561606,0.0070336657,-0.0727923,-0.023166832,0.014397701,0.026844624,0.007273873,0.1235634,0.08868972,0.11233625,0.045767825,-0.081337675,0.042345203,0.07952071,0.06892992,0.01504046,0.02350556,-0.04045694,-0.01736892,-0.015052544,0.03289364,0.040257692,0.010672285,-0.012611962,0.005633374,0.07261969,0.014161681,-0.051126834,0.035710726,-0.003489561,0.051623