	('f9d82a5e-9168-4d1f-9c7b-45eb8c9b4a16', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', 'd287fc3a-06d0-434c-92fd-17e3639dcaf8', 'Training Team Members on Power Word Implementation | Role: Lead | A structured approach for training and coaching associates on effectively using the 10 power words to improve sales performance and customer engagement. | Conduct power words training session | Schedule a 30-minute training session to introduce the 10 power words. Explain the psychology behind each word and provide 2-3 example phrases for each word that associates can use with customers. | Demonstrate through role-playing exercises | Create scenarios where associates practice using power words in different customer situations. Have them practice opening conversations, handling objections, and closing sales using the power words naturally. | Observe associates during customer interactions | Shadow associates during actual customer interactions to observe their use of power words. Take notes on which words they use effectively and which opportunities they miss. | Decision: Provide targeted coaching based on observation | Determine coaching approach based on associate''s performance | Track and review progress weekly | Monitor associate progress by observing interactions and tracking sales metrics. Provide weekly feedback sessions to reinforce successful power word usage and address areas for improvement.', 'd00e17387882b005', '[-0.036417294,0.033189762,-0.029495403,0.026988173,-0.0660664,0.009327437,0.061788276,0.030248053,-0.0054849344,-0.046935283,0.024478134,0.060665276,0.04089282,0.023095643,0.09578948,0.07901205,0.07227801,0.055696238,-0.07092942,-0.04527042,0.04954666,0.0132724745,0.05803845,0.023333803,-0.019041156,-0.017729068,-0.05764686,-0.03107951,0.0323686,0.008795785,-0.035254292,-0.0016526536,0.08769672,0.054367453,-0.026550371,0.056904707,-0.01026486,0.096028134,0.045177303,-0.016365692,-0.059539177,-0.1085572,-0.009606551,-0.012709507,0.03336552,-0.0923281