	('29205099-b972-428a-832d-0ba36215f9cd', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', 'a51c2b73-7551-4b49-b5ac-7336b8a8d938', 'Customer Approach and Engagement Process | Role: New Associate | A structured approach to greeting customers, building rapport, and creating a comfortable shopping environment that encourages engagement and sales. | Prepare Your Approach | Maintain a positive attitude and carry a relevant prop (such as a product sample, accessory, or styling tool) when approaching customers. This gives you a natural conversation starter and professional appearance. | Make Initial Contact | Approach the customer with a personal remark that demands a positive answer to put them at ease. For example, ''That color looks amazing on you!'' or ''You have great timing - we just got this collection in!'' Avoid saying ''Can I help you?'' as it often receives a defensive response. | Engage and Withdraw | After your initial positive interaction, give the customer space to browse. Say something like ''I''ll let you take a look around, and I''ll check back in a few minutes to see how you''re doing.'' | Return and Build Rapport | Return within 3-5 minutes to continue building rapport. Ask open-ended questions that cannot be answered with ''no,'' such as ''What kind of occasion are you shopping for?'' or ''What style are you drawn to today?'' | Decision: Customer Engagement Level | Assess the customer''s level of interest and engagement to determine next steps.', '3c6bf5cf30e10ffc', '[-0.056711897,0.023331268,0.022434382,0.021832425,0.0025570667,-0.028240494,0.08533204,0.058830164,-0.024136795,-0.10107858,0.023556542,-0.02324056,-0.0030243013,-0.014631026,0.0904492,-0.0014898204,0.07946105,0.014081554,-0.0107347015,0.033932593,-0.05287731,-0.05067674,0.06573992,0.028751446,-0.13617995,-0.066512786,0.072005644,0.009930157,0.042949542,-0.0464792,0.0065356507,0.077087805,0.077700086,0.05336325,-0.0761384,0.09203209,0.0341479,0.04601131,-0.0023966176,-0.041622955,-0.0602