	('8332ecd7-00f1-43ab-b0bb-9d47983996ee', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', '6767977f-e752-4a77-976e-a25a97bbd001', 'Inventory Management and Alternative Solutions | Role: Lead | A comprehensive process for handling out-of-stock situations while maintaining sales opportunities and customer satisfaction through alternative solutions. | Know Your Stock | Maintain thorough knowledge of current inventory levels, including sizes, colors, and quantities. Regularly check stock levels and avoid overselling limited items. Update your knowledge daily through inventory reports and floor checks. | Check for Item Availability | When a customer requests a specific item, immediately check both floor inventory and back stock. Use the POS system to verify exact availability including all sizes and color options. | Decision: Item Availability Status | Determine the availability status of the requested item to provide appropriate next steps. | Never Return Empty-Handed | When the exact item is unavailable, present similar alternatives that meet the customer''s needs. Select items with comparable style, price point, or function. Explain the benefits and unique features of the alternative options. | Offer Additional Solutions | Contact other store locations to locate the item, or offer to special order the item if available through the system. Provide clear timelines for availability and follow-up procedures. | Document and Follow Up | Record customer contact information and item details for future follow-up. If special ordering or locating from other stores, provide expected delivery dates and contact the customer when the item arrives.', '67c295fab92d349b', '[0.009389961,0.047815364,-0.01761708,0.05519615,-0.0053397208,0.018658107,-0.0026026687,0.03695494,0.008506802,-0.028342916,0.07901801,0.028260527,-0.03154206,-0.047000863,0.019116817,-0.03823948,0.09795324,-0.0023577833,-0.015972663,-0.06262035,-0.06547248,-0.10357618,-0.008101738,0.02749958,-0.094305605,0.028833