	('1d2f5bd9-4650-430b-8c8f-f006cf6860ea', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', '4f8bd399-4e2c-44e9-979d-568de44b19ae', 'Training New Associates on Customer Greeting Standards | Role: Lead | Train and coach new team members on the Stop and Drop in 15 rule to ensure consistent, positive customer first impressions across the store. | Explain the Stop and Drop in 15 rule | Teach new associates the importance of the 20-second first impression window and demonstrate the three steps: recognize customers within 15 seconds/15 feet, stop and make eye contact with a smile, then drop tasks and approach with a friendly greeting. | Demonstrate proper greeting technique | Model the correct body language, eye contact, smile, and approach for new associates. Show examples of open posture, appropriate distance, and friendly verbal greetings. | Practice with role-playing scenarios | Have the new associate practice greeting different types of customers (rushed, browsing, hesitant) while you observe and provide feedback on timing, body language, and approach. | Monitor and provide feedback during shifts | Observe the associate''s greeting performance during actual customer interactions and provide coaching', '0c5616e8278f52e1', '[-0.0985028,0.010946207,0.04920351,-0.02624705,-0.07509781,-0.024218155,0.0109240115,-0.002411196,-0.024353405,-0.10586678,0.055336393,0.00016342782,-0.03574739,0.0011060057,0.08683127,-0.0037517806,0.06674046,0.035749245,0.0090272995,-0.00025431687,1.7259299e-05,-0.05433021,0.05371615,0.019978654,-0.12122689,-0.0527959,0.030537667,-0.033036403,0.044110637,-0.06300742,-0.04029053,0.03516407,0.13186252,0.015605744,-0.052849423,0.08270566,0.055967093,0.02819514,0.018256081,-0.011179671,-0.05293326,-0.06887952,-0.02627111,0.0015435402,0.0680001,-0.018390793,0.03344179,0.050893966,0.017059553,0.025664032,-0.012289262,-0.0691741,0.058399297,0.05639956,-0.018311359,0.06646551,-0.034627568,-0.005060896,-0.0037117219,0.06904475,-0.056329563,-0.036756597,-0