	('ce3baa49-d2e4-4874-bb80-65a18aa66f3c', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', '2c987af7-7d6e-4c4f-9adb-2785a749e527', 'Add-On Selling Using Picture-Perfect Techniques | Role: New Associate | Learn how to increase sales by painting vivid pictures for customers rather than using generic phrases, using proven storytelling techniques to showcase additional products. | Complete the primary sale | Ensure the customer has selected their main item and is ready to proceed. Confirm their satisfaction with the primary purchase before moving to add-ons. | Choose your add-on approach | Select one of three approaches: 1) Show them something that makes the first purchase better (enhancement approach), 2) Help them avoid future inconvenience (prevention approach), or 3) Generic approach (last resort only). | Decision: Select enhancement or prevention approach | Choose your approach based on the customer''s situation and needs | Paint a vivid picture with specific details | Create a detailed, sensory description of how the add-on item will look, feel, or benefit them. Example: ''We just received a new shipment of Lenna Agnes pieces. I could pair a unique necklace with this outfit to make your friends jealous and ensure you have a one-of-a-kind look.'' | Wait for customer response and proceed accordingly | Give the customer time to visualize what you''ve described, then respond based on their interest level.', 'c0592db4262b29a8', '[-0.063159406,0.063797995,0.056337323,-0.0057862876,-0.027022393,0.0702376,0.05049301,0.07574022,-0.013163279,-0.06903608,0.0938884,0.04645352,0.024296429,-0.011143642,0.0581607,0.017808955,0.09112052,0.008492002,-0.060362887,-0.05833298,-0.0054203817,-0.071954474,0.0272448,0.012109583,-0.063739985,-0.04759474,-0.00720065,0.004941504,0.054406613,-0.06954985,-0.019538675,0.048937883,0.10141198,0.020787554,-0.03376854,-0.03716839,-0.040098686,0.06714135,0.034943953,-0.031322964,0.015047312,-0.09515219,-0.08912407,0.028184745,0.025352146,-0.1359