	('032c3a36-4e14-4494-88f3-38719e7948d3', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', '4c860836-0de8-4558-ae1a-fa63acd7f2cc', 'Handling Customer Concerns and Policy Exceptions | Role: Lead | Step-by-step process for addressing customer concerns while maintaining flexibility with store policies to ensure customer satisfaction. | Acknowledge the customer''s concern | Listen without interrupting and acknowledge their situation with phrases like ''I understand your concern'' rather than dismissive language. | Evaluate policy flexibility options | Consider the customer''s history, the nature of their request, and the potential long-term value of the customer relationship. | Communicate policy with flexibility | Use language like ''Typically our policy is ____, but I want to make this right for you. This is what I can do...'' instead of rigid policy statements. | Implement solution and confirm satisfaction | Execute the agreed-upon solution and ask the customer if the resolution meets their needs before concluding the interaction. | Document exception if applicable | Record any policy exceptions made and the reasoning for future reference and team learning.', 'b4d751e990e29e6a', '[-0.0041395966,0.10626616,0.013559698,0.023174612,-0.0019782356,0.06521263,0.076882556,0.08148615,-0.09168478,-0.055165157,0.058742866,-0.017409144,0.011187532,-0.029314272,0.053973097,0.011762945,0.0013517655,0.0068397643,-0.064732656,0.049311265,-0.01386233,0.007259754,-0.014655864,0.044003837,-0.13391782,-0.0071221148,0.05983511,0.012930696,-0.00013826968,0.024540612,-0.03492322,0.016453546,-0.011323574,-0.010016101,0.04523813,0.028853029,-0.039609957,-0.05757844,-0.028706275,-0.09653166,-0.04075889,-0.03990346,-0.04137314,0.03337426,0.04726874,-0.12667102,0.043972228,-0.038184233,-0.065119356,-0.039865915,-0.049615446,-0.03441852,0.010995989,-0.016935715,0.033734623,-0.014200258,-0.01768022,-0.010523374,0.010002574,-0.034039352,-0.01798198,-0.05140864,-0.06545036,0.03209612,-0.09513014