	('bc37b227-2200-47bb-9f65-f44cafb3771e', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'ai_item', 'd74d886d-a4ff-46ac-ae2b-669908fb7cef', 'Customer Greeting and Initial Engagement | Role: New Associate | A systematic approach to making positive first impressions and building rapport with customers using the ''Stop and Drop in 15'' rule. | Apply the 15-Second Rule | Within 15 seconds of a customer entering the store or coming within 15 feet of you, STOP what you are doing and make eye contact with a genuine smile. | DROP and Approach | DROP your current task, take a few steps toward the customer, and offer a friendly ''Hello!'' with open body posture (body erect, hands away from body). | Initiate Conversation | Use one of the approved greeting options such as ''What brings you in today?'' or ''Tell me what you are shopping for?'' to begin building rapport. | Decision: Customer Response Assessment | Evaluate the customer''s openness to assistance based on their verbal and non-verbal cues. | Provide Business Card | Before the customer leaves, give them a business card with your name written on it for future reference and to encourage return visits.', 'a0093c6eb641fe92', '[-0.07276768,0.0709913,0.058475,-0.0059112636,-0.030069211,-0.03050169,0.07107276,0.024331836,-0.012086369,-0.12755303,0.042151872,-0.02852701,-0.034378964,-0.022907624,0.101543315,0.021383755,0.08447932,0.009973779,-0.021358708,0.040791746,0.0041066995,-0.009235532,0.011124735,0.026745118,-0.11230734,-0.04280699,0.061105188,-0.0093514,0.022141974,-0.037930872,0.008596889,0.073532976,0.11932857,0.009139827,-0.032099746,0.06871005,0.057403933,0.007959294,0.03691851,-0.022224413,-0.025577594,-0.08744885,-0.049831774,0.012158737,0.082907625,-0.086221695,0.03491348,0.065170854,0.035610184,0.036542006,-0.057641022,-0.011743136,0.009207203,0.077148445,-0.02479893,0.06626905,-0.010865788,-0.024900202,0.030434001,0.026391473,-0.041569974,-0.06732631,-0.010980941,0.016857829,-0.06472418,0.005855339,-0.071036205,-0.0