	('d6eeecd2-6940-4a23-9e3e-df7f83bd52ce', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'knowledge_doc', 'd2316b75-9a96-4b5e-9990-a5c7bc9dd0a9:chunk:0', '[Sales Training - 12 Ways to Be Top Salesperson.docx] Sales Training:  The 12 Ways To Be Top Salesperson

Being the top salesperson isn''t hard when you know what the best do. From choosing their attitude, responses to customers, sales style and follow up, these are the steps the best do to consistently exceed their sales goals.

1. Maintain a positive attitude towards yourself and your work. When something goes wrong, don''t waste time complaining but work towards its correction.

2. Understand a clean and organized store directly correlates to high sales.

3. Approach and speak to more customers.

4. Realize that customers are on the defensive. Make a personal remark that demands a positive answer, putting the customer at ease. Never say, "Can I help you?"

5. Carry a prop when approaching a customer and get away quickly to let the customer browse. Return within a few minutes and continue to build rapport.

6. Ask questions that open windows; rarely ask anything that can be answered with a no. For example, "What are you looking for?"

