	('b5609b89-a148-40ec-8c0e-a8eb903244f3', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'knowledge_doc', '019d0c42-e8e3-4486-b69d-a9398fee79b2:chunk:2', '[Tips for Improving Language on the Sales Floor.docx]  Do That"

This is another way of saying "No" and that is the last phrase your customer wants to hear.  

Better Alternative:  "Let me get a manager to take a look at that."  

Manager''s Better Alternative:  "I think the right solution is…"

"We''re Out of That Item"

Customers know that occasionally run out of merchandise.  Encourage them to buy by offering alternative products or take their name and number so you can call them when it is back in stock.  

Better Alternative:  "That item is currently out of stock, but we have a great alternative," or "Well if you don''t like that one as much, I can give you a ring when it''s back in stock.  Is that OK?"

"That is Against Our Policy"

We can''t afford to be inflexible.  Store policies are important because they provide guidelines for how to handle most situations.  It is important to understand the value of a satisfied customer and to make exceptions if needed.  

