Step Two: Now that you have proven your attentiveness and broken the ice with eye contact, DROP whatever you are working on and approach the customer by taking a few steps in their direction and giving them a friendly “Hello!” Make sure to open your posture by having your body erect and moving your hands away from your body.  



By enacting the “Stop and Drop in 15” Rule, you will be well down the road to creating the positive first impression that is so important to getting your customer in the buying mood. 



Greetings and Conversation Starters

“Tell me what you are shopping for?”

“What brings you in today?”

“Are you looking for anything particular that I can help you with?”

 “… well my name is ___, let me know if I can help you with anything.”

“I like your ____, where did you get them?”

“Are y’all having a girl’s day?”

If a man is with them (talk to him, he is usually the one paying) “Do these ladies have you out shopping today?”

