“I love that ____ you chose. It looked so great on you.” – (only say this if the item really did look great on them)

“Do you need help find a shoe in your size?”



Let’s Apply It: Make a list of five original customer greetings and turn in to your manager. It’s always a good idea to have a few greetings in the back of your mind to keep your greetings original.







 



102 – HOW TO QUALIFY YOUR CUSTOMER’S NEEDS

A few common retail mistakes to avoid:



Failing to find out the customer’s requirements of what they need or want. 

Focusing on your own agenda instead of the customer’s.

Not giving customers the majority of air time – let them do the talking.

Confusing “telling” with “selling” – listen to what the customer is saying.

Not being knowledgeable about the product you are selling. You should be able to inform the customer why they need the item. 

Not knowing the prevailing promotions, specials, and regular prices.



