	('ed7cd4a1-7d2d-4a0d-bae2-3333c20ddd0e', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'knowledge_doc', '43ab573c-ea3b-4aed-8499-7b1e2e0e7750:chunk:5', '[Sales Training Manual.docx]  customer’s needs:



Step One: Find out why they are shopping.  If they are shopping to find a specific outfit for an event or are just browsing, customers will enjoy the idea that you care what they are looking for. 



Step Two: Start suggestively selling them items based on your conversation thus far.  Make real conversation with the customer as you suggest items.  Every customer is use to the normal salesperson/customer scenario, so surprise them with a personable, genuine interest in what they need.



Step Three: Continue talking and working with the customer until you have two or three options for them to try. Focus on the clues that the customer has given you through conversation to help you find what they need. 



Let’s Apply It: You will perform two mock sales scenarios with your manager to practice suggestive selling and adapting to customer’s preferences.  





