	('ff76ed79-cb37-478d-82fd-31d997eb0058', 'b0396051-34a1-475b-addc-771e580a5224', 'knowledge_doc', '43ab573c-ea3b-4aed-8499-7b1e2e0e7750:chunk:10', '[Sales Training Manual.docx]  on, you could also ask if they had decided to get the ___ outfit.  This gives you the opportunity to once again give them your opinion.  

Don’t rush the customer to the register right after they get out of the dressing room.  Ask them if you can take the clothes that they already tried on and want and put them behind the register until they are ready.  Don’t linger behind the register because it will make the customer feel rushed. 

Allow them time to browse and possibly even try on more clothes.  If you feel the customer is open to it, suggest jewelry or other complimentary items to what they are buying. 

Let’s Apply It: Focus on suggesting add-on items at the checkout to three of your customers today. 





106 – FOLLOWING UP AND BUILDING REFERRALS

