107 – OVERCOMING OBSTABLES WITH DIFFICULT CUSTOMERS

The customer is ALWAYS right! 

We will not always have the specific item that a customer is looking for; however it is your job to be suggestive and think on your toes in order to persuade the customer in a new direction and save the sale. 

Ways to ensure that we take advantage of every customer that comes into our store with a specific need:

Always offer to check our other locations for the item that they are looking for.  

If that fails, recommend something else that may be similar.  Never come back empty handed.  If something is sold out, present something you think they would like. 

If we don’t have anything remotely like the item, try to figure out why they need the item and find a new solution.

