You should always drop what you are doing to help the customers.  Every single customer counts.

Customers that have negative feedback from our store are far more likely to spread the word than one that has a positive experience.  To avoid this, speak to every customer and offer to help in a friendly manor regardless to how they look or are dressed.  If you offer and a customer doesn’t need help, back off but still be available if they need help.

In retail, business is based on the customers.  If there aren’t customers then there is no business and no one makes money.  This is why it is very important to value and work hard to have good customer relationships. 

The complete customer experience is based on all of the aspects of selling that we have covered.  

Review the steps:

Greet and start conversation 

Start them a dressing room

Suggest add-ons

Follow up in the dressing room

Check out and thank by name

