the fashion industry. She continued to work at Gail''s all through high school and during her college breaks from MSU. Libby began 
going to markets and buying for Gail''s when she was 19. When she graduated from college, she was already managing Gail''s and 
had begun designing and wholesaling her own jewelry line to stores throughout Mississippi. However, she was uncertain as to 
whether she would take one of several department store jobs offered to her in larger cities. Not wanting to sacrifice her creativity, 
she decided to open her own store. 
